<dl id="s17027w"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17027w">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s17all.htm#s17027w">sector 27(w)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hide in perfumed cellar.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To preserve themselves from so many dangers, and in accordance with the physicians&apos; orders, numbers of frightened people <mark>shut themselves up in tightly closed and perfumed cellars</mark>, where they awaited the decrees of Fate. The approach of the phenomenon increased the panic, and it is said that one village cur&eacute;, being unable to hear the confessions of all his flock, who wanted to discharge their souls of sin before taking flight for a better world, was fain to tell them &ldquo;there was no hurry, because the eclipse had been put off a fortnight on account of the number of penitents&rdquo;! <small> Camille Flammarion, <a name="CFAA" href="/udra/udex.htm#CFAA"><cite title="source">Astronomy for Amateurs</cite></a> (1904), 268</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
